{
  "texts": [
    "The capsule takes on the role of a neuron in this situation.",
    "CNs describe an input at the component level and assign a vector to each component.",
    "This vector's length indicates the possibility of a component's existence, and it replaces max pooling with \"routing by agreement.\"",
    "Because capsules are self-contained, the likelihood of accurate classification improves when numerous capsules agree on the same criterion.",
    "A weighted matrix W i,j rotating and translating a posture vector u i,j to a vector U i can be used to represent each component."
  ]
}